<br>
A Magician can contribute to a raid in five ways:<br>
<br>
1. Preparation and wipeout recovery: summoned stuff<br>
2. Melee damage (pet)<br>
3. Debuff (Malise spell line, Cancel Magic spell line)<br>
4. Nukes (Fire and Magic based)<br>
5. Call of the Hero (player summoning across the zone)<br>
<br>
Summoned stuff is a way to prepack mana into useful things in<br>
advance. It does not even cost a spell component. It does cost,<br>
however, a lot of mana, especially when I have to supply a whole raid.<br>
<br>
I am very happy to contribute to a raid by summoning before it starts.<br>
Makes me feel useful and needed.<br>
<br>
Like every caster, during the raid I want to use my mana for activity:<br>
Summon pet, debuff, nuke, eventually the mana and component costly<br>
CotH. If I have to summon stuff for other people, I can't use my mana<br>
to summon pets, to debuff, to nuke. If you wait with asking for<br>
summoned stuff until after the raids start, you do so at the expense of<br>
my ability to contribute to the raid in active ways.<br>
<br>
Every mod rod you pick up before the raid means one mod rod less to<br>
summon for me during the raid. That is why I want EVERYONE to pick up a<br>
mod rod when I summon them, so the clerics can be supplied at all the<br>
time, especially in difficult moments and on wipeout recovery. Even<br>
better is when you get one each of modrod1 and modrod2.<br>
<br>
Here are some numbers:<br>
<br>
My mana pool is about 2500 (at level 55).<br>
<br>
225 mana: One modrod1.<br>
400 mana: One modrod2.<br>
160 mana: Each piece of summoned stuff.<br>
<br>
Depending on occasion, typically people request up to 2 or 3 pieces of<br>
summonable armor, which means I have to spend about 900 mana per<br>
caster and 625 mana per non-caster person. With one full bar of mana I<br>
can supply about 4 people. Even with C2 it takes about 5 minutes to<br>
recover fully. That means, in about 40 minutes I can outfit a<br>
30-person-raid if I don't use mana for anything else. All those things<br>
are lore items, however, so I can't prepare before meeting you.<br>
<br>
Raid useful summonable things:<br>
<br>
- Mod rod (225HP to 175 mana)<br>
- Rod of Mystical Transvergance (modrod2, level 56, 300HP to 220 mana, 3 charges)<br>
- Elemental Blanket: Resist 15 FR, 15MR, 15CR shoulder/back item (lore)<br>
- Shard of the Core: Resist 15 CR, 15 PR Ultravision range item<br>
- Fast cast ring<br>
- Hard nuke bracelet<br>
- Reduce spell component consumption necklace<br>
- Longer Buff duration shoulders (buff spell caster needs to wear)<br>
- Reduce mana consumption earring<br>
<br>
All effects on the last 5 items are by about 1-20%.<br>
<br>
There is one behaviour that really annoys me: I see folks hanging out<br>
at the meeting point, I call that I am summoning stuff (and I tend to<br>
spam so that everyone sees it) ... and I hardly get a reaction. Then<br>
later, when it gets urgent, when I want to be active, at least ten of<br>
people come to me: Can you summon this, can you summon that for me?<br>
Grrrrr. Honestly, I am close to the point to deny summoned stuff during<br>
raids. If you didn't pick it up before the raid when I was calling out<br>
that I summon ... tough luck for you.<br>
